snippet.textDisplay:
Truly speaking, arnob shouldn't have given the part in the second season. Through thick and thin, first season saw his prime and he did great. I might sound opinionated but it was high time they moved their arrangement and production to other type of renditions. Pritom and Emon Chowdhury were a relief of fresh air, but then again, here comes Arnob and co, same cliche composition, same saxophone and same electronic music in every song. And the worst part of this is he maintains his circle around coke studio, it's more like arnob and friends. his nepo vibe, actually ruining the songs to some extend. 
The type is getting cliche and boring. It's high time for Arnob to take a break and let other composers do their things.
